parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as the vehicle suddenly accelerates without the driver's input.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates at a high rate of speed
the vehicle lunges forward from a parked position
the vehicle accelerates out of control
the vehicle goes into reverse or forward gear without driver input
the engine races when first started.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: the vehicle is unable to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water pump failure can cause engine overheating, leading to costly repairs, engine damage, or even engine failure.
Camshaft failure can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, engine failure, or even engine seizure.
The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power steering and braking ability, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the battery warning light is illuminated
the vehicle experiences a sudden loss of power
the vehicle is unable to start.
